    "This allows us to utilize the dual of a hypergraph to simplify the construction process.",
    "The dual of a hypergraph is simply another hypergraph, where the nodes and hyperedges are interchanged, as shown in Figure 2.",
    "Using the duality feature, we first model the documents as nodes and keywords as hyperedges to construct the document hypergraph H D. The keyword hypergraph H C can then be easily constructed by taking the dual of H D. This construction process also allows us to map user interactions on documents and keywords to operations on a single hypergraph (DC1).",
    "Even better, the duality feature between documents and keywords matches the user's mental model (DC3), making the visualization and interaction intuitive.2) Hierarchical Clustering: Once the two hypergraphs are constructed, we separately hierarchically cluster them using an agglomerative clustering algorithm.",
    "Clusters in the document hypergraph represent topics that are discussed in the dataset."
